<section><title>File Options</title>
<para>
Offers methods to manage loading and exporting to/from this specific Aggregate layer.
</para>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Load External Layers</guilabel></term>
<listitem>
<para>
Using this forces External Layers in this Aggregate Layer to be loaded and so contribute to analysis, as otherwise they are loaded only when they are displayed or selected.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Open File as External Layer...</guilabel></term>
<listitem>
<para>This opens a dialog to select files to <xref linkend="open_external"/> within this Aggregate Layer.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Save Layer As...</guilabel></term>
<listitem>
<para>This opens a dialog to choose a name and location for a new Viking file containing data just this Aggregate Layer.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Append File...</guilabel></term>
<listitem>
<para>This opens a dialog to select files to load within this Aggregate layer.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Export As GPX...</guilabel></term>
<listitem>
<para>This opens a dialog to choose a name and location for a new GPX file from all visible <xref linkend="TrackWaypoint"/> layers in this Aggregate Layer into a single GPX file.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Export via GPSBabel...</guilabel></term>
<listitem>
  <para>This opens a dialog to choose options for the export using <application>GPSBabel</application>.
    Internally it converts all the geo-data in the Aggregate layer into a single temporary GPX file for use in exporting to whatever format you choose.</para>
  <para>It is only available if <application>GPSBabel</application> is detected.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</section>

<section><title>Tracks Area Coverage</title>
<para>
  Offers methods related to Tracks Area Coverage.
</para>
<variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
    <term><guilabel>Calculate</guilabel></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Start a new TAC calculation.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
    <term><guilabel>Increase/Decrease</guilabel></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Changes the TAC square size appropriately and performs a recalculation with the new value.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
    <term><guilabel>Goto</guilabel></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Even though the analysis of squares have a variance of colours, it may not be obvious where they are - especially if outside the current viewport.
        Thus these options recenter the viewport on the center of the selected analysis type.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
    <term><guilabel>Remove</guilabel></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        This clears the Tracks Area Coverage information, thus no grid colouring will be displayed.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</section>

<section><title>Tracks Heatmap</title>
<para>
  Offers methods related to the Heatmap.
</para>
<variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
    <term><guilabel>Calculate</guilabel></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Start a new heatmap calculation for current area displayed on the viewport.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
    <term><guilabel>Remove</guilabel></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Clear the heatmap from the display.
      </para>
    </listitem>
